"{\"uid\": \"thegatewaypundit.com-2024-07-google-hit-backlash-sides-soul-crushing-olympics-commercial\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"No matter their political leanings, most human beings bristle at the mere suggestion that machines might effectively replace them.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On social media over the weekend, viewers of thealready repellentOlympic Games channeled their inner Luddite in visceral reactions towards a commercial for Google's Gemini AI feature - a commercial that one user on the social media platform X described as \\\"soul crushing.\\\"\", \"from\": 132, \"to\": 404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, Google's Olympic advertisement struck at the heart of what it means to be human.\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 414, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ironically, the minute-long commercial began in one of the most charming ways imaginable.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The voice of a proud father accompanied pictures and videos of a young girl who loves to run.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, in the innocent way that children do, the young girl idolizes American Olympic hurdler Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 753, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996805940469343, \"rank\": 0.00031833004356415, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998948915219, \"rank\": 1.0507132479627366e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She might even be the world's number one Sydney fan,\\\" the father said of his daughter.\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 848, \"end\": 854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998948915219, \"rank\": 1.0507132479627366e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in a preview of its impending dark turn, the commercial showedGemini AIhelping the young girl look up proper running and hurdling techniques.\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, that part did not disturb viewers.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But what came next most certainly did.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She wants to show Sydney some love, and I am pretty good with words, but this has to be just right,\\\" the father said.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998948915219, \"rank\": 1.0507132479627366e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ensuing sequences showed the father promptingGemini AIto help his daughter write a fan letter to McLaughlin-Levrone.\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yikes.\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adverse reactions came swiftly, even from liberal sources broadly associated with ananti-human woke ideology.\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, on the social media platform Bluesky, NPR podcast hostLinda Holmespanned the Google ad.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.852974057181772e-12, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero SUCKS.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1645, \"end\": 1647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obviously there are special circumstances and people who need help, but as a general \\\"look how cool, she did not even have to write anything herself!\\\"\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"story, it SUCKS.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who wants an AI-written fan letter??\\\"\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Holmes wrote.\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1895, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999999211095232, \"rank\": 7.88905129379151e-08, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This commercial showing somebody having a child use AI to write a fan letter to her hero SUCKS.\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Obviously there are special circumstances and people who need help, but as a general \\\"look how cool, she did not even have to write anything herself!\\\"\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"story, it SUCKS.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who wants an AI-written fan letter??\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- Linda Holmes (@lindaholmes.bsky.social)Jul 27, 2024 at 8:48 AM    On X, Professor Shelly Palmer of Syracuse University's Newhouse School of Public Communications called it \\\"one of the most disturbing commercials I have ever seen.\\\"\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.590414995820572e-25, \"text\": \"Linda Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly Palmer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly_Palmer\"}, {\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"score\": 0.999999973968443, \"rank\": 1.541531028193864e-08, \"text\": \"Syracuse University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syracuse_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, Palmer added that the commercial depicts \\\"exactly what we do not want anyone to do with AI.\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2543, \"end\": 2545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ever.\\\"\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Have you seen Google's \\\"Dear Sydney\\\" Olympic ad featuring a father using Gemini AI to help his young daughter write a fan letter to Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone?\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998948915219, \"rank\": 1.0507132479627366e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is one of the most disturbing commercials I have ever seen.\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be clear, I love the idea of a young aspiring athlete\\u2026pic.twitter.com/FFohdVBbut  - Shelly Palmer (@shellypalmer)July 29, 2024    Meanwhile, freelance writer Kaitlyn Arford described the Google ad as the worst thing about the games thus far.\", \"from\": 2777, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2938, \"end\": 2945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.9957241429440393, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaitlyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\"}, {\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\"}, {\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trending:WATCH: No-Nonsense Judge TORCHES Violent Teen Robber and Gives Him a Harsh Sentence, Causing Thug's Family to Completely Lose It  \\\"I think we can all agree that the big loser of the #Olympics is the Google Gemini AI ad where they think an AI-written letter is better than a sweet note from a young girl to her favorite athlete,\\\" Arford posted.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 3245, \"end\": 3247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think we can all agree that the big loser of the#Olympicsis the Google Gemini AI ad where they think an AI-written letter is better than a sweet note from a young girl to her favorite athlete.\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 3450, \"end\": 3456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.07308217781245e-14, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- Kaitlyn Arford - Freelance Writer (@kaitarford)July 28, 2024    When ranking the Olympics' worst moments, Arford might have overlooked theblasphemous opening ceremonies.\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3575, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"score\": 0.9957241429440393, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaitlyn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaitlyn_(wrestler)\"}, {\"begin\": 3583, \"end\": 3589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\"}, {\"begin\": 3681, \"end\": 3687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Arford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Otherwise, one cannot argue with her objection.\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3792, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another social media user called the ad \\\"one of the worst possible use cases for AI I can imagine.\\\"\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Way to teach your kid they do not need to have an original thought or a genuine interaction with another human,\\\" the user added.\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 4024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Google Gemini letter writing commercial is one of the worst possible use cases for AI I can imagine.\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4030, \"end\": 4036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9999992683231488, \"rank\": 7.31668998798574e-07, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 4037, \"end\": 4043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Way to teach your kid they do not need to have an original thought or a genuine interaction with another human.\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- Sidney Pegula (@sidneypegula)July 28, 2024    Finally, another social media user compared the \\\"soul crushing\\\" ad to a recent Apple iPad commercial \\\"where the message was supposed to be a sign of progress but instead kills those special 'human' moments together.\\\"\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4378, \"end\": 4382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"score\": 0.9939931505267938, \"rank\": 0.006043149764335439, \"text\": \"iPad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The@GoogleGemini commercial where a father prompts Gemini to draft a letter to Olympian Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone for his daughter is not as charming as intended IMO.\", \"from\": 4511, \"to\": 4677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4562, \"end\": 4568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999780588624742, \"rank\": 2.194161899123178e-05, \"text\": \"Gemini\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gemini_Awards\"}, {\"begin\": 4590, \"end\": 4598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\", \"score\": 0.6661173454359107, \"rank\": 0.31542147728692327, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twelve_Olympians\"}, {\"begin\": 4599, \"end\": 4605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998948915219, \"rank\": 1.0507132479627366e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of some beautiful commercial showing the journey where a father helps his daughter find her voice in\\u2026pic.twitter.com/BvRXxlS43y  - Michael R. (@ImpactForward)July 29, 2024    TheApplead in question showed musical instruments, video games, books and even ancient busts being crushed by a giant press then disappearing amid the splattering of paint.\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 5034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, the press lifted to reveal a sleek new iPad.\", \"from\": 5035, \"to\": 5085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5080, \"end\": 5084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"score\": 0.9939931505267938, \"rank\": 0.006043149764335439, \"text\": \"iPad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The intended message, of course, was that Apple's product combines all of those other tangible things into one device.\", \"from\": 5089, \"to\": 5207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5131, \"end\": 5136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5811349906340365e-15, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like theGooglead, however, it simply missed the mark.\", \"from\": 5208, \"to\": 5261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the aptly named business-and-technology news outletTechCrunch, the Apple ad sparked a similarly adverse reaction.\", \"from\": 5263, \"to\": 5389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5343, \"end\": 5348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5811349906340365e-15, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it did so for the same reason.\", \"from\": 5390, \"to\": 5424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What Apple seems to have forgotten is that it is the things in the real world - the very things Apple destroyed - that give the fake versions of those things value in the first place,\\\" Devin Coldewey wrote for TechCrunch.\", \"from\": 5426, \"to\": 5648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5432, \"end\": 5437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5811349906340365e-15, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 5523, \"end\": 5528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5811349906340365e-15, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 5637, \"end\": 5647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TechCrunch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TechCrunch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, people seldom take kindly to the idea that real things do not matter.\", \"from\": 5650, \"to\": 5727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nor do they react well to messages that even hint at the obsolescence of any human experience.\", \"from\": 5729